$ Oracle: Chains
@ chain

A *chain* is a (named) series of programs that are linked together for a combined object. A chain is created with `dbms_scheduler.create_chain`.

Rules can be added to a chain with `define_chain_rule`.

Attributes of a chain include
  • pause
  • paused_before
  • skip
  • restart_on_failure
  • restart_on_recovery
  • destination_name (See `all_scheduler_external_dests` and `all_scheduler_db_dests`)
  • credential_name

sa:
  `→ development/databases/Oracle/installed/packages/dbms/scheduler`
